# JSX: conditional render with `&&`

When the **false** branch renders **nothing**, prefer **logical AND** over a ternary with **`null`**:

```tsx
// ✅ Prefer
{isVisible && (
  <>
    <Title />
    <Body />
  </>
)}

// ❌ Avoid (when the else branch is only null)
{isVisible ? (
  <>
    <Title />
    <Body />
  </>
) : null}
```

- Use a **fragment** (`<>…</>`) when the conditional block has **multiple roots**; a **single child** does not require a fragment (`{show && <Item />}` is fine).
- **Precompute** a **boolean** for long conditions (see **Precompute Complex Conditions** in TypeScript coding style), then `{thatBoolean && (…)}`.
- **Exceptions:** keep a **ternary** (or `if` / early return) when the **else** branch renders **different UI**, not empty.

**Caveat:** Do not use `&&` when the left-hand value can be a **number** like `0` (React will render `0`). Use explicit boolean (`count > 0 && …`) or ternary.
